Former Liverpool manager Graeme Souness, now a television pundit, called the Gunners "weak and insipid".
"I'm never surprised by the criticism that comes," said Wenger.
"Part of the opinion is always a bit excessive and emotional, but we have to deal with that and I don't complain about it.
"I think people are a bit too emotional and we want to put things into perspective by analysing things a bit more in a neutral way."
